<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-259-010  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 259 010.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>DG Review  May 1989 v9 n11 p48(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Text retrieval systems.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Jacobs, Paula.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Text retrieval software is capable of free-form search orretrieval of any word or string of words from a textual database.andO;It has become an important component of integrated businessautomation systems.andP;  Text retrieval systems such as DG-LIBRARYhave practical applications and can save time in such areas aspersonnel administration, corporate communications anddocumentation departments.andP;  DG-LIBRARY's design and operation aredescribed.andP;  Text retrieval systems can vary considerably in priceand functionality.andP;  In selecting a system users should considerwhether software under evaluation offers full-text capabilitiesand how closely it matches their requirements.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Information Storage and RetrievalSoftware PackagesText Data BasesOffice AutomationFree-Text Searching.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>